---
import ServiceLayout from '../../layouts/ServiceLayout.astro';
---

<ServiceLayout 
  title="Dental Scaling & Root Planing" 
  category="Preventive Care"
  description="Think of scaling as a deep cleaning of the teeth. Having your teeth scaled for tartar is an important part of visiting the dentist to maintain healthy gums."
  image="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1606811841689-23dfddce3e95?w=1920&h=600&fit=crop"
>
  
  <!-- Main Content -->
  <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
    <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-accent-100 to-accent-200/50 border-l-4 border-accent-300 p-6 rounded-r-lg mb-8">
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-dental-charcoal mb-2">Deep Cleaning for Healthy Gums</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-0">
        Think of scaling as a deep cleaning of the teeth. Having your teeth scaled for tartar – 
        a sticky deposit on teeth in which bacteria grow – is an important part of visiting the dentist. 
        This thorough cleaning helps prevent gum disease and maintains your oral health.
      </p>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-3xl font-heading font-semibold text-dental-charcoal mb-6">
      What is Dental Scaling?
    </h2>
    
    <div class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-md p-8 mb-12">
      <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
        Dental scaling is a thorough cleaning procedure that removes plaque and tartar (calculus) from above 
        and below the gum line. When combined with root planing, it's often called a "deep cleaning" and is 
        the primary non-surgical treatment for gum disease.
      </p>
      
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-4">Understanding Plaque vs. Tartar</h3>
          <div class="space-y-4">
            <div class="bg-yellow-50 border-l-4 border-yellow-300 p-4">
              <h4 class="font-semibold text-yellow-800 mb-2">Plaque</h4>
              <p class="text-yellow-700 text-sm">
                Soft, sticky film of bacteria that forms on teeth daily. Can be removed with proper brushing and flossing.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-300 p-4">
              <h4 class="font-semibold text-red-800 mb-2">Tartar (Calculus)</h4>
              <p class="text-red-700 text-sm">
                Hardened plaque that has mineralized and cannot be removed with home care. Requires professional scaling tools.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-4">Why Tartar is Problematic</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-3">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-red-500 mt-0.5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M8.257 3.099c.765-1.36 2.722-1.36 3.486 0l5.58 9.92c.75 1.334-.213 2.98-1.742 2.98H4.42c-1.53 0-2.493-1.646-1.743-2.98l5.58-9.92zM11 13a1 1 0 11-2 0 1 1 0 012 0zm-1-8a1 1 0 00-1 1v3a1 1 0 002 0V6a1 1 0 00-1-1z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
              </svg>
              <span>Provides rough surface for more bacteria to attach</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-red-500 mt-0.5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M8.257 3.099c.765-1.36 2.722-1.36 3.486 0l5.58 9.92c.75 1.334-.213 2.98-1.742 2.98H4.42c-1.53 0-2.493-1.646-1.743-2.98l5.58-9.92zM11 13a1 1 0 11-2 0 1 1 0 012 0zm-1-8a1 1 0 00-1 1v3a1 1 0 002 0V6a1 1 0 00-1-1z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
              </svg>
              <span>Causes gum inflammation and bleeding</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-red-500 mt-0.5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M8.257 3.099c.765-1.36 2.722-1.36 3.486 0l5.58 9.92c.75 1.334-.213 2.98-1.742 2.98H4.42c-1.53 0-2.493-1.646-1.743-2.98l5.58-9.92zM11 13a1 1 0 11-2 0 1 1 0 012 0zm-1-8a1 1 0 00-1 1v3a1 1 0 002 0V6a1 1 0 00-1-1z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
              </svg>
              <span>Leads to gum disease progression</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-red-500 mt-0.5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M8.257 3.099c.765-1.36 2.722-1.36 3.486 0l5.58 9.92c.75 1.334-.213 2.98-1.742 2.98H4.42c-1.53 0-2.493-1.646-1.743-2.98l5.58-9.92zM11 13a1 1 0 11-2 0 1 1 0 012 0zm-1-8a1 1 0 00-1 1v3a1 1 0 002 0V6a1 1 0 00-1-1z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
              </svg>
              <span>Can cause bad breath and tooth loss</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-red-500 mt-0.5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M8.257 3.099c.765-1.36 2.722-1.36 3.486 0l5.58 9.92c.75 1.334-.213 2.98-1.742 2.98H4.42c-1.53 0-2.493-1.646-1.743-2.98l5.58-9.92zM11 13a1 1 0 11-2 0 1 1 0 012 0zm-1-8a1 1 0 00-1 1v3a1 1 0 002 0V6a1 1 0 00-1-1z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
              </svg>
              <span>Linked to heart disease and other health issues</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-3xl font-heading font-semibold text-dental-charcoal mb-6">
      Types of Scaling Procedures
    </h2>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 mb-12">
      <!-- Regular Cleaning -->
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-green-50 to-green-100/30 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-green-800 mb-4">Prophylaxis (Regular Cleaning)</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
          Standard cleaning for patients with healthy gums, removing plaque and tartar from above the gum line.
        </p>
        
        <h4 class="font-semibold mb-2">When It's Recommended:</h4>
        <ul class="space-y-1 text-gray-600 text-sm mb-4">
          <li>• Healthy gums with minimal bleeding</li>
          <li>• Routine maintenance every 6 months</li>
          <li>• Light to moderate tartar buildup</li>
          <li>• No deep pockets around teeth</li>
        </ul>
        
        <div class="bg-green-100 rounded-lg p-3">
          <p class="text-sm text-green-800">
            <strong>Duration:</strong> 30-60 minutes, usually comfortable with minimal sensitivity
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Deep Cleaning -->
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-primary-50 to-primary-100/30 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-4">Scaling & Root Planing (Deep Cleaning)</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
          Comprehensive cleaning that addresses gum disease by cleaning below the gum line and smoothing root surfaces.
        </p>
        
        <h4 class="font-semibold mb-2">When It's Needed:</h4>
        <ul class="space-y-1 text-gray-600 text-sm mb-4">
          <li>• Signs of gum disease (gingivitis/periodontitis)</li>
          <li>• Pockets deeper than 4mm around teeth</li>
          <li>• Heavy tartar buildup below gums</li>
          <li>• Bleeding, swollen, or receding gums</li>
        </ul>
        
        <div class="bg-primary-100 rounded-lg p-3">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
            <strong>Duration:</strong> 1-4 appointments, local anesthetic typically used for comfort
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-3xl font-heading font-semibold text-dental-charcoal mb-6">
      The Deep Cleaning Process
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6 mb-12">
      <!-- Step 1 -->
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-primary-50 to-primary-100/30 rounded-xl p-6">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-primary-900 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
            <span class="text-white font-bold">1</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-2">Assessment & Preparation</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600 mb-3">
              We measure pocket depths around your teeth, take X-rays if needed, and explain the treatment plan. 
              Local anesthetic is applied to ensure your comfort during the procedure.
            </p>
            <div class="bg-primary-100 rounded-lg p-3 text-sm text-gray-700">
              <strong>Pocket depths:</strong> 1-3mm healthy, 4-6mm moderate disease, 7mm+ advanced disease
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Step 2 -->
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-accent-50 to-accent-100/30 rounded-xl p-6">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-accent-300 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
            <span class="text-primary-900 font-bold">2</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-dental-charcoal mb-2">Scaling</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600 mb-3">
              Using specialized instruments, we remove plaque and tartar from tooth surfaces above and below 
              the gum line. This may involve hand instruments, ultrasonic scalers, or both.
            </p>
            <div class="bg-accent-100 rounded-lg p-3 text-sm text-gray-700">
              <strong>Tools used:</strong> Hand scalers, curettes, ultrasonic scalers, air polishing devices
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Step 3 -->
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-primary-50 to-primary-100/30 rounded-xl p-6">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-primary-900 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
            <span class="text-white font-bold">3</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-2">Root Planing</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600 mb-3">
              The root surfaces are smoothed to remove bacterial toxins and create a clean surface that 
              allows gums to heal and reattach to the teeth.
            </p>
            <div class="bg-primary-100 rounded-lg p-3 text-sm text-gray-700">
              <strong>Goal:</strong> Smooth root surfaces promote gum healing and prevent bacteria reattachment
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Step 4 -->
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-accent-50 to-accent-100/30 rounded-xl p-6">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-accent-300 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
            <span class="text-primary-900 font-bold">4</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-dental-charcoal mb-2">Follow-up Care</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600 mb-3">
              We may apply antimicrobial agents to treated areas and schedule follow-up appointments to monitor 
              healing. Home care instructions are provided to maintain results.
            </p>
            <div class="bg-accent-100 rounded-lg p-3 text-sm text-gray-700">
              <strong>Recovery:</strong> Healing typically occurs within 1-2 weeks with proper home care
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-3xl font-heading font-semibold text-dental-charcoal mb-6">
      Signs You May Need Scaling
    </h2>

    <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-red-50 to-red-100/30 rounded-2xl p-8 mb-12">
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
        Don't wait for pain to seek treatment. Gum disease is often painless in early stages, 
        but these signs indicate you may need professional scaling:
      </p>
      
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-red-800 mb-4">Early Warning Signs</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-3">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <div class="w-5 h-5 bg-red-500 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">
                <span class="text-white text-xs">!</span>
              </div>
              <span>Bleeding gums when brushing or flossing</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <div class="w-5 h-5 bg-red-500 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">
                <span class="text-white text-xs">!</span>
              </div>
              <span>Red, swollen, or tender gums</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <div class="w-5 h-5 bg-red-500 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">
                <span class="text-white text-xs">!</span>
              </div>
              <span>Persistent bad breath or metallic taste</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <div class="w-5 h-5 bg-red-500 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">
                <span class="text-white text-xs">!</span>
              </div>
              <span>Visible tartar buildup (yellow/brown deposits)</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-red-800 mb-4">Advanced Symptoms</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-3">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <div class="w-5 h-5 bg-red-700 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">
                <span class="text-white text-xs">⚠</span>
              </div>
              <span>Receding gums or teeth appearing longer</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <div class="w-5 h-5 bg-red-700 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">
                <span class="text-white text-xs">⚠</span>
              </div>
              <span>Loose or shifting teeth</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <div class="w-5 h-5 bg-red-700 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">
                <span class="text-white text-xs">⚠</span>
              </div>
              <span>Pain when chewing</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <div class="w-5 h-5 bg-red-700 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">
                <span class="text-white text-xs">⚠</span>
              </div>
              <span>Pus between teeth and gums</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-3xl font-heading font-semibold text-dental-charcoal mb-6">
      After Your Scaling Treatment
    </h2>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-12">
      <div class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-md p-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-4">What to Expect</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-600">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-blue-500 mt-0.5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
              <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M18 10a8 8 0 11-16 0 8 8 0 0116 0zm-7-4a1 1 0 11-2 0 1 1 0 012 0zM9 9a1 1 0 000 2v3a1 1 0 001 1h1a1 1 0 100-2v-3a1 1 0 00-1-1H9z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
            </svg>
            <span>Some sensitivity to hot/cold for a few days</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-blue-500 mt-0.5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
              <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M18 10a8 8 0 11-16 0 8 8 0 0116 0zm-7-4a1 1 0 11-2 0 1 1 0 012 0zM9 9a1 1 0 000 2v3a1 1 0 001 1h1a1 1 0 100-2v-3a1 1 0 00-1-1H9z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
            </svg>
            <span>Minor bleeding during brushing is normal initially</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-blue-500 mt-0.5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
              <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M18 10a8 8 0 11-16 0 8 8 0 0116 0zm-7-4a1 1 0 11-2 0 1 1 0 012 0zM9 9a1 1 0 000 2v3a1 1 0 001 1h1a1 1 0 100-2v-3a1 1 0 00-1-1H9z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
            </svg>
            <span>Gums may feel tender for several days</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-blue-500 mt-0.5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
              <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M18 10a8 8 0 11-16 0 8 8 0 0116 0zm-7-4a1 1 0 11-2 0 1 1 0 012 0zM9 9a1 1 0 000 2v3a1 1 0 001 1h1a1 1 0 100-2v-3a1 1 0 00-1-1H9z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
            </svg>
            <span>Teeth may feel different or "loose" temporarily</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-md p-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-4">Home Care Instructions</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-600">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-accent-300 mt-0.5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
              <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
            </svg>
            <span>Use desensitizing toothpaste if needed</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-accent-300 mt-0.5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
              <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
            </svg>
            <span>Rinse with warm salt water 2-3 times daily</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-accent-300 mt-0.5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
              <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
            </svg>
            <span>Continue gentle brushing and flossing</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-accent-300 mt-0.5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
              <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
            </svg>
            <span>Avoid hard, sticky, or spicy foods initially</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-3xl font-heading font-semibold text-dental-charcoal mb-6">
      Maintaining Results
    </h2>

    <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-accent-50 to-accent-100/30 rounded-2xl p-8 mb-12">
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
        Scaling and root planing can halt gum disease progression and restore gum health, but maintaining 
        results requires ongoing commitment to oral hygiene and regular professional care.
      </p>
      
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Daily Home Care</h4>
          <ul class="text-sm text-gray-600 space-y-1">
            <li>• Brush twice daily with soft-bristled toothbrush</li>
            <li>• Floss daily to remove plaque between teeth</li>
            <li>• Use antimicrobial mouthwash</li>
            <li>• Consider water flosser for deeper cleaning</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Professional Maintenance</h4>
          <ul class="text-sm text-gray-600 space-y-1">
            <li>• More frequent cleanings (3-4 months)</li>
            <li>• Periodontal maintenance appointments</li>
            <li>• Regular pocket depth monitoring</li>
            <li>• X-rays to check bone levels</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Lifestyle Factors</h4>
          <ul class="text-sm text-gray-600 space-y-1">
            <li>• Don't smoke or use tobacco</li>
            <li>• Manage diabetes and stress</li>
            <li>• Eat a balanced, nutritious diet</li>
            <li>• Stay hydrated for healthy saliva flow</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-primary-900 text-white rounded-2xl p-8">
      <h3 class="text-2xl font-heading font-semibold mb-4">
        Protect Your Gums & Overall Health
      </h3>
      <p class="mb-6">
        Healthy gums are essential for overall health. Professional scaling removes harmful bacteria 
        and toxins that can't be reached with home care alone. Don't let gum disease progress untreated.
      </p>
      <a href="#book-appointment" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-accent-300 text-primary-900 px-6 py-3 rounded-full font-medium hover:bg-accent-200 transition-colors">
        Schedule Your Deep Cleaning
        <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 5l7 7-7 7" />
        </svg>
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Related Services -->
  <div slot="related-services" class="space-y-3">
    <a href="/services/ultrasonic-scaling" class="block p-3 rounded-lg hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors">
      <h4 class="font-semibold text-dental-charcoal">Ultrasonic Scaling</h4>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Advanced scaling with ultrasonic technology</p>
    </a>
    <a href="/services/general-dentistry" class="block p-3 rounded-lg hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors">
      <h4 class="font-semibold text-dental-charcoal">General Dentistry</h4>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Comprehensive preventive care</p>
    </a>
    <a href="/services/periodontal-therapy" class="block p-3 rounded-lg hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors">
      <h4 class="font-semibold text-dental-charcoal">Periodontal Therapy</h4>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Advanced gum disease treatment</p>
    </a>
  </div>

  <!-- FAQ -->
  <div slot="faq" class="space-y-6">
    <details class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-6">
      <summary class="font-semibold text-lg cursor-pointer">Is dental scaling painful?</summary>
      <p class="mt-4 text-gray-600">
        Most patients experience little to no discomfort during scaling. For deeper cleanings, we use 
